      "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\">Dr. Umesh is conducting a workshop on health education and promotion. While discussing the components of attitude, he lists several elements. Which of the following is NOT typically considered a component of attitude?</span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q8583262",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 34627,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
      "subjects_id": [
        7
      ],
      "solution": "<p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Ans. D. Motivation</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Option D:</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Attitude&nbsp;</strong>is <strong>permanent</strong> way of <strong>behaviors</strong> based on <strong>objective organization</strong> of beliefs on <strong>object / person / situation.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Explanation:&nbsp;</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\">Attitude includes <strong>three components: (ABC Model of attitudes include Affective, Behavioural and cognitive)</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Option A.&nbsp;</strong>A <strong>cognitive or knowledge element</strong>: The <strong>beliefs, thoughts</strong> and <strong>knowledge</strong> an individual <strong>holds</strong> about the <strong>object</strong> of their <strong>attitude.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Option B.&nbsp;</strong>An <strong>affective or feeling element:</strong> The <strong>emotional or affective</strong> response a person has toward the <strong>object</strong> of <strong>their attitude</strong>. It involves the <strong>feelings</strong> and <strong>emotions</strong> associated with the <strong>subject.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Option C.&nbsp;Behavioural</strong> tendencies: The individual's <strong>actions </strong>or intentions toward the <strong>object </strong>of their <strong>attitude</strong>.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Educational objective:&nbsp;</u></strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong>Attitude&nbsp;</strong>consists of <strong>three components</strong>: a <strong>cognitive </strong>element encompassing <strong>beliefs</strong> and <strong>knowledge </strong>about the <strong>attitude object</strong>, an BOLD element involving <strong>emotional responses</strong> towards <strong>it </strong>and a <strong>behavioral tendency</strong> indicating the <strong>individual's actions</strong> or <strong>intentions </strong>related to the <strong>object.</strong></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><span style=\"font-size:12pt;\"><strong><u>Ref</u>: Park 26<sup>th</sup> ed pg. 766</strong></span></p>",
